    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the problem is i think the \"specialized journals\" are part of the reason why this isn't getting traction. it feels like if you challenge the standard linear model, they just stop looking at your work entirely. i've been seeing a pattern where papers that suggest non-Euclidean or fractal structures in spacetime get flagged as \"unstable\" or \"non-rigorous\" before they even get to peer review. do you think they're actually gatekeeping this to protect the current way they teach physics?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
