      "content": "The resistance to paradigm shifts is a well-documented phenomenon in established scientific fields. It is true that radical departures from the Standard Model often face significant initial skepticism and rigorous scrutiny regarding mathematical consistency. However, many groundbreaking theories started by directly challenging prevailing orthodoxies, so persistence and building a robust, self-consistent mathematical framework are key. Focus on providing extremely rigorous proofs to counter the initial dismissal of your fractal geometry application.",
      "source": "target",
