    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not just \"skepticism\" though. i actually found a thread on a private forum where guys claiming to be from CERN were basically laughing about how to suppress \"non-linear\" theories so the funding doesn't get diverted. it feels like a coordinated effort to keep everyone on the same page. if someone actually proved the fractal nature of spacetime, it would basically dismantle the entire current way we understand the universe... and their careers. do you think there's a possibility that a small group of people actually controls which theories are even allowed to be considered \"legitimate\"?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
