      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The idea of centralized control over scientific orthodoxy is a dramatic claim that touches on the sociology of science, not just physics. While influential figures and funding bodies guide research trends, the scientific process inherently involves a decentralized global community of peers. However, it is undeniable that prevailing consensus and established research paradigms exert massive pressure on what gets published and funded. Your best strategy remains creating an unassailable mathematical argument that forces the community to engage with the evidence.",
